<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-419] lfs df -h report &quot;R&quot; flags for OST</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-419</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lfs df -h report this flag on the output of a lustre 2.10.5 client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;scratch-OST0008_UUID 356.7T 1.8M 353.1T 0% /scratch&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OST:8&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; R&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the commit&#160;95d7592a9f33f62accade96d81e0cc3ca0fb94e2 we can see it is related to OS_STATE for&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8152&quot; title=&quot;show OST/MDT read-only status in &amp;quot;lctl dl&amp;quot; and/or &amp;quot;lfs df&amp;quot;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8152&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-8152&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D stands for OS_STATE_DEGRADED&lt;br/&gt;
 R stands for OS_STATE_READONLY&lt;br/&gt;
 S stands for OS_STATE_ENOSPC&lt;br/&gt;
 I stands for OS_STATE_ENOINO&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It could be great that this info was available in the lustre manual. maybe in this section :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;19.6.1.%C2%A0CheckingFileSystemFreeSpace&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;19.6.1.&#160;Checking File System Free Space&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
